there is no longer any point in shaking the mercury down, and the thermometer is carelessly left lying on the bedtable, where an assembly of books that has come to congratulate you and a few playthings (idle onlookers) are crowding out the half-empty bottles of turbid potions.

A writing case with my note paper

Is what I most vividly see:

The leaves are adorned with a horseshoe

And my monogram. I had become

Quite an expert in twisted initials,

Intaglio seals, dry flattened flowers

